"title": "1115: God, purpose of",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "1115",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>God has a plan for his creation which he will certainly accomplish. It is carried out through the control of circumstances and his choice and use of people, and above all in the life, death, resurrection and second coming of Jesus Christ.</p>\n<h2>God's purpose will be accomplished</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa46:10-Isa46:11\">ISA 46:10–46:11</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps135:6\">PSA 135:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov16:4\">PRO 16:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eccl3:14\">ECC 3:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa14:24\">ISA 14:24</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa14:26-Isa14:27\">ISA 14:26–14:27</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa25:1\">ISA 25:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa55:11\">ISA 55:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph1:11\">EPH 1:11</a></p>\n<h2>God's purpose prevails</h2>\n<h3>It stands for ever</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps33:11\">PSA 33:11</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job42:2\">JOB 42:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer23:20\">JER 23:20</a></p>\n<h3>It cannot be thwarted by human beings</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov19:21\">PRO 19:21</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job9:12\">JOB 9:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job23:13\">JOB 23:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa8:10\">ISA 8:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan4:35\">DAN 4:35</a></p>\n<h3>It cannot be thwarted by evil powers</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev17:17\">REV 17:17</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam16:14\">1SA 16:14</a> <em>The implication is that evil is subject to God's control and operates within the determined limits of his sovereign purpose</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job1:12\">JOB 1:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job2:6\">JOB 2:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor12:7\">2CO 12:7</a></p>\n<h3>It prevails in people's lives and circumstances</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov16:9\">PRO 16:9</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov20:24\">PRO 20:24</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov21:1\">PRO 21:1</a></p>\n<h3>It is fulfilled through his choice of individuals</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph1:11\">EPH 1:11</a></strong> <em>God's choice of individuals does not invalidate their free will to do or not to do anything, nor remove their answerability to God for their actions.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen18:19\">GEN 18:19</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom11:5\">ROM 11:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor1:1\">1CO 1:1</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph1:4-Eph1:5\">EPH 1:4–1:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Thess2:13\">2TH 2:13</a></p>\n<h3>Examples of the actions of evil people serving God's purpose</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts2:23\">ACT 2:23</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen50:20\">GEN 50:20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa10:5-Isa10:7\">ISA 10:5–10:7</a></p>\n<h2>God's purpose is founded on divine wisdom</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph3:10-Eph3:11\">EPH 3:10–3:11</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps104:24\">PSA 104:24</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom11:33\">ROM 11:33</a></p>\n<h2>God's purpose is determined from eternity</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Tim1:9\">2TI 1:9</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs19:25\">2KI 19:25</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa25:1\">ISA 25:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa46:10\">ISA 46:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt25:34\">MAT 25:34</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph1:4\">EPH 1:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Titus1:2\">TIT 1:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet1:20\">1PE 1:20</a></p>\n<h2>God's purpose is for his own glory</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod9:16\">EXO 9:16</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom9:17\">ROM 9:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek36:22-Ezek36:23\">EZK 36:22–36:23</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph1:5-Eph1:6\">EPH 1:5–1:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph1:11-Eph1:12\">EPH 1:11–1:12</a></p>\n<h2>God's purpose for his people</h2>\n<h3>God reveals his purpose to his people</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Amos3:7\">AMO 3:7</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen18:17\">GEN 18:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam7:20-2Sam7:21\">2SA 7:20–7:21</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor2:9-1Cor2:10\">1CO 2:9–2:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph1:9\">EPH 1:9</a></p>\n<h3>Its fulness is beyond human understanding</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom11:33\">ROM 11:33</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut29:29\">DEU 29:29</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor2:9-1Cor2:10\">1CO 2:9–2:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph1:9\">EPH 1:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph3:4-Eph3:5\">EPH 3:4–3:5</a></p>\n<h3>It is good and loving</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom8:28\">ROM 8:28</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer29:11\">JER 29:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom12:2\">ROM 12:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph1:4-Eph1:5\">EPH 1:4–1:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Tim1:9\">2TI 1:9</a></p>\n<h2>God's purpose is revealed through Jesus Christ</h2>\n<h3>In the church</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph3:10-Eph3:11\">EPH 3:10–3:11</a></strong></p>\n<h3>It centres on the cross</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa53:10\">ISA 53:10</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts4:27-Acts4:28\">ACT 4:27–4:28</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet1:19-1Pet1:20\">1PE 1:19–1:20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1John4:10\">1JN 4:10</a></p>\n<h3>It is God's purpose to redeem the world through the cross</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt26:18\">MAT 26:18</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt26:45\">MAT 26:45</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark14:41\">MRK 14:41</a> <em>Jesus Christ often speaks of his appointed “hour”.  In John's Gospel in particular his “hour” refers to the cross.  Jesus Christ refuses to allow anything except the cross to be the climax of his ministry (<a href=\"https://ref.ly/John12:27\">Jn 12:27</a>).</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John7:6-John7:8\">JHN 7:6–7:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John12:23\">JHN 12:23</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John13:1\">JHN 13:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John17:1\">JHN 17:1</a></p>\n<h3>It is God's purpose to exalt and establish Jesus Christ as Lord</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph1:9-Eph1:10\">EPH 1:9–1:10</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts2:36\">ACT 2:36</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phil2:8-Phil2:11\">PHP 2:8–2:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col1:18\">COL 1:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb1:2-Heb1:4\">HEB 1:2–1:4</a></p>\n<h3>Jesus Christ submits to God's purpose</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John6:38\">JHN 6:38</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt26:39-Matt26:42\">MAT 26:39–26:42</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark14:35-Mark14:36\">MRK 14:35–14:36</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke22:42\">LUK 22:42</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John4:34\">JHN 4:34</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John5:30\">JHN 5:30</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb5:7-Heb5:8\">HEB 5:7–5:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb10:7\">HEB 10:7</a></p>\n<h2>God's ultimate purpose is to save</h2>\n<h3>The salvation of people through Jesus Christ</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John6:40\">JHN 6:40</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John3:16-John3:17\">JHN 3:16–3:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal1:3-Gal1:4\">GAL 1:3–1:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim2:3-1Tim2:4\">1TI 2:3–2:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet1:2\">1PE 1:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Pet3:9\">2PE 3:9</a></p>\n<h3>Specific aspects of God's purpose in salvation</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor5:5\">2CO 5:5</a> <em>knowing heavenly life</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom8:29\">ROM 8:29</a> <em>being conformed to Jesus Christ</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph1:4\">EPH 1:4</a> <em>being holy and blameless</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph2:15\">EPH 2:15</a> <em>becoming unified</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph3:10-Eph3:11\">EPH 3:10–3:11</a> <em>that the wisdom of God be revealed</em></p>\n<h2>God wills that people submit to his purposes</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jas4:15\">JAS 4:15</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps40:8\">PSA 40:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps143:10\">PSA 143:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt6:10\">MAT 6:10</a></p>\n<h2>God's people should pray for the fulfilment of his purposes</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt6:9-Matt6:10\">MAT 6:9–6:10</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke11:2\">LUK 11:2</a></p>\n<h2>People can reject God's purposes in their lives</h2>\n<p><em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke7:30\">LUK 7:30</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke19:41-Luke19:42\">LUK 19:41–19:42</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts13:46\">ACT 13:46</a></p>\n<h2>Examples of God's purposes being worked out</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen45:5-Gen45:9\">GEN 45:5–45:9</a> <em>in the life of Joseph</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa41:2\">ISA 41:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa41:25\">ISA 41:25</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa45:1\">ISA 45:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa45:13\">ISA 45:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa46:11\">ISA 46:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa48:14\">ISA 48:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts18:21\">ACT 18:21</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts21:14\">ACT 21:14</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom1:10\">ROM 1:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom15:32\">ROM 15:32</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor4:19\">1CO 4:19</a></p>",
